summary: Actor Danny Trejo, known for his role in "Machete," was involved in a physical altercation during the Fourth of July parade in Sunland-Tujunga, Los Angeles. The incident reportedly occurred after Trejo was hit by a water balloon, leading to a confrontation with the individual responsible. The fight escalated, resulting in Trejo throwing a chair and being knocked to the ground. Trejo alleges that the perpetrator acted in a cowardly manner, while witnesses reported that he had been drinking alcohol prior to the event. name: Coco Gauff
summary: American tennis sensation Coco Gauff has made a strong start at the Wimbledon Championships, defeating Caroline Dolehide in the first round and advancing to the third round. Gauff has a long history with Wimbledon, having reached the fourth round in 2019 and the final 16 in 2021. She is considered a rising star in the sport, and her performances at this year's tournament have been impressive. She is set to face fellow American Emma Navarro in the third round. Gauff's success at Wimbledon also brings attention to her grandmother, who was the first Black student at a Palm Beach County high school. Gauff believes that all players have an equal chance of winning at Wimbledon this year, highlighting the growing depth of talent in women's tennis.

name: Toni Kroos
summary: Toni Kroos' retirement plans have been put on hold as Germany advanced to the quarterfinals of Euro 2024, delaying his departure from the national team. Despite Germany's subsequent defeat to Spain, Kroos remains an integral part of the team and denies any imminent retirement. While some speculate that this may be his final tournament, Kroos insists he will continue to play at the top level. Despite being highly praised for his performance at Euro 2024, Kroos remains committed to his club, Real Madrid, and aims to disappoint his teammates on the Spanish national team who are eager to see him retire. Fans gave him a standing ovation as he left the pitch, acknowledging his illustrious career and his ongoing influence on the game.

name: META stock
summary: Meta Platforms, the parent company of Facebook, has experienced mixed market performance recently. Meta's stock declined amidst allegations of violating EU antitrust laws. However, analysts remain optimistic about its long-term prospects. Meta's recent earnings report and progress in artificial intelligence (AI) have contributed to a surge in its stock price. Experts see Meta as a stronger AI investment compared to Google's parent company, Alphabet. Analysts predict a potential rise in Meta's stock value to $600 due to its AI advancements. Despite its stock's positive performance Monday, it still underperformed the broader market. However, Meta's stock remains under consideration for a split in 2024, indicating a positive outlook for investors.
